et short (most short in 26 weeks), with concentration on the short side rising 9.6pp over the month \u2014 the top 8 traders now hold 48% of short OI. This is a deeply crowded structural short. Critically, this has occurred *against* a +6.8% weekly price move, meaning shorts are being squeezed. The fragility here is acute: forced short-covering could amplify further upside violently. Qualify \u2014 this reflects futures positioning only, not total institutional exposure.\n\n**US10Y** AM positioning sits at the **92nd percentile** net long, with continued buying over the past month (+3.6pp). Dealers are near their most net short in 26 weeks (4th percentile), warehousing the other side of structural buying. This is a high-conviction rates signal \u2014 pension and insurance money is extending duration aggressively, consistent with recession hedging or liability matching in a falling-rate regime. The trade is crowded but likely sticky given the mandate-driven nature of AM flows.\n\n**CAD** long concentration has surged \u2014 top 4 traders now hold 54.8% of long OI, up 16pp over the month. Dealers are net long CAD (hedging client shorts), while HFs sit at just the 46th percentile short. This asymmetric concentration on the long side in a single instrument is fragile and warrants close monitoring.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CROSS-INSTRUMENT THEMES\n\nRates and equities are telling contradictory stories: **US10Y** AM longs (recession signal) clash with equity futures prices rallying hard. **CHF** AM positioning is at the **96th percentile** net short \u2014 unusual for a safe-haven, suggesting AM may be fading the CHF safe-haven bid even as equities sold off. **YEN** short concentration is building (short OI top 8 up 8.8pp monthly), consistent with carry trade reconstruction. FX and rates together point toward USD weakness and global risk caution, while the equity price action screams relief rally.\n\n---\n\n## 4. KEY RISKS\n\n- **NASDAQ short squeeze escalation**: HF shorts at 26-week extremes into a rising market \u2014 any sustained bid forces mechanical covering and amplifies vol\n- **Duration unwind**: If inflation data reverses the rates rally, AM's crowded US10Y long (92nd pctl) unwinds in a thin market with dealers already net short\n- **CAD concentration snap**: A single large participant dominates CAD longs; any policy shift (tariffs, BoC) could trigger a disorderly unwind with limited offsetting liquidity"}